## Membership plans (VX) widget

The **Membership plans (VX)** widget is used to display [membership plans](docs.getvoxel.io_articles_membership-plans_.md) you created.

This widget should be placed in the Pricing page of the [user role(s)](docs.getvoxel.io_articles_membership-roles_.md) you make available. Each role, has its own separate pricing page.

You can create and edit this pricing page in **WP admin Structure  User Roles  Edit role  Paid members tab** **** **Pricing page template**

The pricing page requires **Membership plans (VX)** widget to be added to it.

This pricing page is utilized in various ways. For example, if you enable plan selection during user registration, then the pricing page will be used in the registration flow. The same page can be accessed post registration when user wishes to view or switch their membership plan.

The widget has various configuration and styling settings.

## Price groups

As a membership plan can have [multiple prices](docs.getvoxel.io_article_membership-plans_.md) for different periods, the widget lets you pick the periods which you want to display. Each group creates a tab and displays the relevant plans within that tab.

For example, we can create one group where we display Monthly plans and the other groups for Annual plans. If you need to display multiple prices on the same group, you can pick multiple periods under Choose prices.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Once you create the groups and pick the prices, all the relevant plans will be listed in the widget options

![](data:image/png;base64,)

For each plan, you can upload an image, add a list of features and description.

Once your configuration is complete, you can head to the **Style tab** to adjust the styling, columns and other visual settings related to how the plans are displayed.
